article.headline: Liberty 86, Cincinnati Christian 55
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Seth Curry scored 21 points, and was one of five Liberty players in double figures in an 86-55 rout of Cincinnati Christian on Sunday. Brolin Floyd added 14 points while Tyler Baker, Jesse Sanders and Anthony Smith scored 10 apiece for the Flames (10-4). Floyd also added nine rebounds, four assists and two blocks. Curry was 5 of 9 from beyond the arc. Jake Santel scored 15 points to lead the Eagles (7-5), who counted the game as an exhibition. Nathanael Harney also added 11 points. The Flames shot 50.7 percent from the field (34 of 67) in the game compared to a 35.7 percent mark (20 of 56) for the Eagles. Liberty jumped out of the gates with an 11-3 run, extended that lead to 23-8 on a Sanders tip-in midway through the first and led 46-22 at the break. The Flames scored 44 points in the paint and tallied 12 steals in the win.
